@5044 = ~Adventures with the Child of Bhaal gave Eddard Silvershield a new purpose. They taught him how to be a strong person and brought back the confidence that slavers had taken away from him. He returned to the city of Baldur's Gate, to his family, who welcomed him with open arms. His father was especially happy to see him. Having heard the tales of <CHARNAME> and Eddard's adventures, Entar Silvershield never even tried to undermine their work. Instead, he planned his next move with his son. Eddard also became the Hero of Baldur's Gate, but he found his own ways to support the city he was born in. Still, that didn't stop him from leaving the estate every now and then... on an adventure, of course, to see the world and again taste the kind of life he had while he worked with <CHARNAME>.~
@5045 = ~Adventures with the Child of Bhaal gave Eddard Silvershield a new purpose. They taught him how to be a strong person and brought back the confidence that slavers had taken away from him. He returned to the city of Baldur's Gate, to his family, who welcomed him with open arms. They also welcomed Master Barkshield, of course. Eddard's father was especially happy to see his son back. Having heard the tales of <CHARNAME> and Eddard's adventures, Entar Silvershield never even tried to undermine their work. Instead, he planned his next move with his son. Eddard also became the Hero of Baldur's Gate, but he found his own ways to support the city he was born in. Still, that didn't stop him from leaving the estate every now and then... on an adventure, of course, with Master Barkshield as his trusted companion, to see the world and taste that kind of life he had while he worked with <CHARNAME>.~
@5046 = ~Adventures with the Child of Bhaal gave Eddard Silvershield a new purpose. They taught him how to be a strong person and brought back the confidence that slavers had taken away from him. He returned to the city of Baldur's Gate together with his beloved <CHARNAME>... His family gladly welcomed both of them. His father was especially happy to see his son back and accepted who he fell in love with. Having heard the tales of <CHARNAME> and Eddard's adventures, Entar Silvershield never even tried to undermine their work. Instead, he planned his next move with his son. Eddard also became the Hero of Baldur's Gate, but he found his own ways to support the city he was born in. Still, that didn't stop him from leaving the estate every now and then... with <CHARNAME>, of course. They set off on all kinds of adventures and fought all kinds of monsters. Some tales mention their fight with a powerful Brass Dragon Lord and his army! They won and yet again showed the people of Toril that together, they can fight every creature... and win.~
@5047 = ~Adventures with the Child of Bhaal gave Eddard Silvershield a new purpose. They taught him how to be a strong person and brought back the confidence that slavers had taken away from him. He returned to the city of Baldur's Gate together with his beloved <CHARNAME> and Master Barkshield... His family gladly welcomed all of them. His father was especially happy to see his son back and accepted who he fell in love with. Having heard the tales of <CHARNAME> and Eddard's adventures, Entar Silvershield never even tried to undermine their work. Instead, he planned his next move with his son. Eddard also became the Hero of Baldur's Gate, but he found his own ways to support the city he was born in. Still, that didn't stop him from leaving the estate every now and then... with <CHARNAME> and Master Barkshield, of course. They set off on all kinds of adventures and fought all kinds of monsters. Some tales mention their fight with a powerful Brass Dragon Lord and his army! They won and yet again showed the people of Toril that together, they can fight every creature... and win.~
@5048 = ~The Child of Bhaal broke Eddard's heart by choosing <PRO_HISHER> heritage over their relationship without even breaking up with Eddard first. Even though Eddard did his best to forgive <CHARNAME>, he could not accept this situation. He became bitter and rarely stayed at the Silvershield estate. He set off on... adventures that would keep him busy. Tales say he has thrown himself into less meaningful "relationships" that were nothing else but causal sex, sometimes with people he barely knew. That was yet another way of trying to forget, but... it's not easy when you truly love someone who's gone.~




